sql:
SELECT COUNT(parameter_id) 
FROM algorithm_parameters 
WHERE algorithm_id = 0;

SELECT block_name, description
FROM adjustment_blocks
ORDER BY block_name ASC;

SELECT block_name, description
FROM adjustment_blocks
WHERE input_format = 'JPEG' AND output_format = 'JPEG';

external_knowledge:
- 'transformation wizard' refers to an algorithm of type 'transform';
- 'cast its spell' refers to the execution of the algorithm;
- 'spell on an integer register' refers to the algorithm processing integer data types;
- 'faster than the average speed of all spells' refers to the execution time being less than the average execution time of all algorithms in the `algorithm_performance` table.

- Performance ranking is based on the execution time of the algorithms, with higher execution times indicating lower performance;
- User preferences are ranked by the date they were set, with the most recent preferences having a higher rank;
- Setting changes are ranked by the date they were made, with the most recent changes having a higher rank.

- "Custom settings" refer to user-specific configurations for hardware or software components;
- "Adjustment blocks" are modules responsible for specific functionalities, such as image quality improvement;
- "Registers" are memory locations that store configuration data for the adjustment blocks;
- "Bits" are individual binary units within a register that control specific features.

- 'Administrators' are users with the role 'administrator';
- 'Custom value' is a user-defined setting value;
- 'Average custom value' is the mean of all custom values in the `user_preferences` table;
- 'Settings' are configurations within adjustment blocks;
- 'Adjustment blocks' are components that users can configure.

- "frequently used" refers to settings that have been used more than once;
- "average execution time" is the mean time taken to execute the algorithm;
- "rank by their average execution time" means the algorithms are ordered from the longest to the shortest average execution time.

- "setting_id" uniquely identifies each setting in the system;
- "custom_value" is a user-defined value for a specific setting;
- "preference_date" is the date when the user set a preference;
- "change_date" is the date when the setting was last changed.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT s.block_id) AS distinct_blocks_with_settings
FROM settings s
JOIN adjustment_blocks ab ON s.block_id = ab.block_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'user_id' refers to the unique identifier for a user in the system;
- 'change_date' records the date when a setting was changed;
- 'setting_history' table logs all changes made to user settings.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM setting_history 
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
